paws 0.1.10

Creates a new OriginEndpoint record

Source: R/mediapackage_operations.R
mediapackage_create_origin_endpoint.Rd

Creates a new OriginEndpoint record.

mediapackage_create_origin_endpoint(Authorization, ChannelId,
  CmafPackage, DashPackage, Description, HlsPackage, Id, ManifestName,
  MssPackage, Origination, StartoverWindowSeconds, Tags, TimeDelaySeconds,
  Whitelist)

Arguments

Authorization
ChannelId

[required] The ID of the Channel that the OriginEndpoint will be associated with. This cannot be changed after the OriginEndpoint is created.
CmafPackage
DashPackage
Description

A short text description of the OriginEndpoint.
HlsPackage
Id

[required] The ID of the OriginEndpoint. The ID must be unique within the region and it cannot be changed after the OriginEndpoint is created.
ManifestName

A short string that will be used as the filename of the OriginEndpoint URL (defaults to "index").
MssPackage
Origination

Control whether origination of video is allowed for this OriginEndpoint. If set to ALLOW, the OriginEndpoint may by requested, pursuant to any other form of access control. If set to DENY, the OriginEndpoint may not be requested. This can be helpful for Live to VOD harvesting, or for temporarily disabling origination
StartoverWindowSeconds

Maximum duration (seconds) of content to retain for startover playback. If not specified, startover playback will be disabled for the OriginEndpoint.
Tags
TimeDelaySeconds

Amount of delay (seconds) to enforce on the playback of live content. If not specified, there will be no time delay in effect for the OriginEndpoint.
Whitelist

A list of source IP CIDR blocks that will be allowed to access the OriginEndpoint.
